{{BLP sources|date=March 2013}} {{use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox person | image = AssumptaSerna.jpg | caption = Serna in 2011 | birth_name = María Asunción Rodés Serna | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1957|9|16|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]] | occupation = [[Actor|Actress]] | years_active = 1978–present | spouse = [[Scott Cleverdon]] (1993–present) }}
'''Assumpta Serna''' (born '''María Asunción Rodés Serna''', 16 September 1957), is a [[Spain|Spanish]] actress and author. Born in [[Barcelona]], Serna has performed in 20 different countries in six languages and is the recipient of more than 20 international awards.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=Il9wlNbjyC4C&pg=PA167&dq=nostradamus+assumpta&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwio2MGYtdXQAhWHWxoKHa3kCP8Q6AEIHDAA#v=onepage&q=nostradamus%20assumpta&f=false |title=Assumpta Serna |author=Nuria Vidal |page=167|website=Books.google.es |date= |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
==Biography== Serna was born in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geneall.net/H/per_page.php?id=2161071 |title=María Asunción Rodés Serna, * 1957 |website=Geneall.net |date=1957-09-16 |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref> She studied law until she was 19, after which she "preferred being an [[anarchist]]" and joined the Barcelona's School of Dramatic Arts.<ref>{{cite news|last1=GOLDSTEIN|first1=PATRICK|title=Love, Anarchy--Passions of Assumpta Serna|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1988-07-17/entertainment/ca-9833_1_assumpta-serna|accessdate=3 December 2016|work=Los Angeles Times|date=17 July 1988}}</ref> In 1993, she married her co-star in ''[[Sharpe's Company (TV programme)|Sharpe's Company]]'', [[Scott Cleverdon]], who portrayed [[Harry Price (fictional character)|Lieutenant Harry Price]] in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.todocoleccion.net/coleccionismo-revista-hola/revista-hola-n-2598-ano-1994-carlona-monaco-boda-assumpta-serna-scott-cleverdon-manzanares~x53514169 |title=revista hola nº 2598 año 1994. carlona de monac - Comprar Revista Hola en todocoleccion - 53514169 |website=Todocoleccion.net |date=2007-04-23 |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
==Acting career== In her career as an actress, Serna felt she was more successful in foreign countries than in her own country. Speaking in a 2016 interview,<ref name=elespanol.com/> she said: {{Verse translation|{{lang|es|A veces siento vergüenza de ser española y pienso que esto no hay quien lo enderece... Como actriz me siento desaprovechada en mi país pero muy aprovechada fuera}}|Sometimes I feel ashamed to be Spanish and I think that there is no one who can fix it... As an actress I feel wasted in my country but outside, I can give my best.|attr1=Assumpta Serna<ref name=elespanol.com>{{cite news|title=Assumpta Serna: "La menopausia me costó un año de depresión y otro para salir de ella"|url=http://www.elespanol.com/reportajes/entrevistas/20161111/169983257_0.html|accessdate=3 December 2016|work=El Español}}</ref>}}
===Film=== Serna is known for her starring role in ''[[I, the Worst of All]]'' (1990) portraying famous Mexican religious scholar [[Sor Juana]]. She co-starred with [[Antonio Banderas]] in ''[[Matador (film)|Matador]]'' (1986), one of the first films by [[Pedro Almodóvar]],<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=w4LzeUZ03vQC&pg=PA470&dq=matador+assumpta+serna,+pauline+kael&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiv6tP0tNXQAhVLOxoKHZ8MBd4Q6AEIHDAA#v=onepage&q=matador%20assumpta%20serna%2C%20pauline%20kael&f=false |title=5001 Nights at the Movies |author=Pauline Kael |page=470|website=Books.google.es|accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref> and she appeared in such films as ''[[Wild Orchid (film)|Wild Orchid]]'' (1990), ''[[Chain of Desire]]'' (1992), ''[[Nostradamus (film)|Nostradamus]]'' (1994), ''[[The Shooter (1995 film)|The Shooter]]'' (1995), ''[[The Craft (film)|The Craft]]'' (1996) and ''[[Kiss & Tell (1996 film)|Kiss & Tell]]'' (1997).
Although she predominantly played European roles, Serna has also played [[Colombia|Colombians]] in the films ''Managua'' with [[Louis Gossett Jr.]] and ''Drug Wars'' in [[Michael Mann]]'s series.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.es/books?id=RxHbPxbBM1AC&pg=PP280&lpg=PP280&dq=michael+mann+and+assumpta+serna&source=bl&ots=AVZYEi32D2&sig=UBuViC0nFBBxWaNRoZeGTueO5T8&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=michael%20mann%20and%20assumpta%20serna&f=false |title=Variety TV REV 1991-92 17 - Prouty |page=280 |format=PDF |date=2016 |website=Talentsguadalajara.com |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
Her most-recent movie is ''[[¡He matado a mi marido!]]'' (filmed October–November 2016) directed by [[Francisco Lupini Basagoiti]], with [[María Conchita Alonso]] and [[Eduardo Yañez]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hematadoamimarido.com/crew/ |title=Crew — ¡He matado a mi marido! |website=Hematadoamimarido.com |date= |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://amadoresdelcine.blogspot.com.es/2016/10/la-actriz-espanola-assumpta-serna.html |title=Los Amadores Del Cine: La Actriz Española Assumpta Serna Protagoniza La Comedia "He Matado A Mi Marido", De Francisco Lupini-Basagoiti |publisher=Amadoresdelcine.blogspot.com.es |date=2016-11-06 |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
===Television=== On the small screen, Serna is known for playing a Spanish [[guerrilla]] in the first four of [[ITV Network|ITV]]'s [[Sharpe (TV series)|Sharpe series]] of television films based on the novels of [[Bernard Cornwell]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://islantillacineforum.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/falcon-crest.jpg |format=JPG |title=TP |website=Islantillacineforum.files.wordpress.com |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref> an Italian role in ''[[Falcon Crest]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qlDALjminQI |title=Falcon Crest Opening Complete Guest Cast |publisher=[[YouTube]] |date=2014-06-01 |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref> and portraying [[Catherine of Aragon]] in ''[[Henry VIII (TV serial)|Henry VIII]]'' opposite [[Helena Bonham Carter]] and [[Ray Winstone]]. She also acted on the popular Spanish TV series ''[[Aquí no hay quien viva]]''. From 2011 to 2014, Serna played one of the female leads, [[Vannozza dei Cattanei]], mistress of Cardinal Rodrigo Borgia, in [[Tom Fontana]]'s historical drama ''[[Borgia (TV series)|Borgia]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mundoplus.tv/noticias/?seccion=series&id=5320|title="Borgia" llega a Cosmopolitan TV|website=Mundoplus.tv|accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
She co-produced with Wildcard UK a documentary called ''[[Fresco Fiasco]]'' and acted in the movie ''[[Behold the Monkey]]'', two films about the famous restoration of the ''[[Ecce Homo (Elías García Martínez)|Ecce Homo]]'' which attracted more than 200,000 visitors from 170 countries to the little town of Borja to see the painting. Both projects were seen in February 2016 on the ''[[Sky Arts]]'' network in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WTXITZE-J94 |title=Estreno del Documental "Fresco fiasco" |publisher=[[YouTube]] |date=2016-07-07 |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://go.sky.com/tvboxsets/series/content/series/d95b451480903510VgnVCM1000000b43150a____ |format=PDF |title=SKY Box Sets |date=2016 |website=Go.sdky.com |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.es/espana/aragon/abci-eccehomo-borja-salta-television-britanica-201606171248_noticia.html |title=El Eccehomo de Borja salta a la televisión británica |website=Abc.es |date=2016-06-17 |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
==Educator and other work== Serna has written two books on acting technique: ''Screen acting'' or ''El trabajo del actor de cine'' (1999), which was the first book to be written in Spanish regarding the craft of film-acting,<ref>{{cite book|title=El trabajo del actor de cine|trans-title=The Work of the Actor|last=Serna|first=Assumpta|date=1999|publisher=Catedra|language=Spanish|ISBN=978-8437617053}}</ref> and ''Monologues in V.O.'' (2001), a resource for auditioning actors.
Serna currently teaches courses on communication and leadership in English and Spanish. Serna and Cleverdon developed the first university Master course for actors on "Screenacting". With the collaboration of more than 70 international organizations and workshops around the world, they teach the courses "Directing Actors" and "The Script and the Actor".{{citation needed|date=December 2016}}
They formed Fundación First Team<ref name=fund/>{{failed verification|date=December 2016}} and, since 2000, have taught 4,000 students in 6 countries in collaboration with various film schools and film festivals. The last workshop was at the [[Guadalajara International Film Festival]] in Mexico.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.talentsguadalajara.com/descargas/Programa-TALENTS-EN.pdf |format=PDF |title=Programa de Actividades |date=2016 |website=Talentsguadalajara.com |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>{{failed verification|date=December 2016}} Foundation First Team always include disabled and under-privileged people in their courses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europapress.es/epsocial/ong-y-asociaciones/noticia-sector-discapacidad-pide-no-quedar-fuera-series-tv-20150521145955.html |title=El sector de la discapacidad pide no quedar fuera de las series de TV |language=Spanish |website=Europapress.es |date=2015-05-21 |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
Through Foundation First Team, Serna has published ''First Female directors of Spanish movies'', written by Conchita Martínez Tejedor.<ref name=fund>{{cite web|url=http://www.fundacionfirstteam.org |title=Cursos Interpretación Cinematográfica : Escuela actores first team |website=Fundacionfirstteam.org |date=2014-06-20 |accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>{{failed verification|date=December 2016}}
Serna served as President of AISGE (Actores e Intérpretes – Sociedad de Gestión de España), Spain's society of managing [[intellectual property|intellectual property rights]] for actors.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=qy6La_j0Ee0C&pg=PA129&dq=aisge,+assumpta+serna&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwij66Pnt9XQAhXF5xoKHf0EAPYQ6AEIMTAB#v=onepage&q=aisge%2C%20assumpta%20serna&f=false |title=Bibliografia espańola sobre Propiedad Intelectual 1987-2000 |author=César Iglesias Rebollo|page=129 |website=Books.google.es|accessdate=2016-12-02}}</ref>
She has volunteered in many organizations, such as the [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS), where for four years she helped select foreign movies for the Oscars. She was a board member of the [[European Film Academy]] (EFA) for eight years, and raised 1.8 million euros to bring the European film awards to Catalunya in 2004.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}}
