{{distinguish|Journal of Near Eastern Studies}} {{Infobox journal | title = Journal of the Ancient Near Eastern Society | cover = | former_name = The Journal of the Ancient Near Eastern Society of Columbia University | editor = | discipline = | language = | abbreviation = | publisher = | country = | history = 1968-present | frequency = Biannually | website = https://janes.scholasticahq.com/ | link1 = | link1-name= | ISSN = 0010-2016 | LCCN = | OCLC = 730040442 }} The '''''Journal of the Ancient Near Eastern Society''''' is a biannual [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]]. It was established in 1968 as ''The Journal of the Ancient Near Eastern Society of Columbia University'', and since 1980 it has been housed at the [[Jewish Theological Seminary of America]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Journal of the Ancient Near Eastern Society (JANES)|url=http://www.etana.org/node/10605|website=Electronic Tools and Ancient Near East Archives|accessdate=11 October 2015}}</ref> The most recent issue appeared in 2011. The journal is abstracted and indexed in [[ATLA Religion Database]].<ref name=ATLA>{{cite web |url=https://www.atla.com/products/titles/Pages/default.aspx |title=Title and Product Update Lists |publisher=[[American Theological Library Association]] |work=[[ATLA Religion Database]] |accessdate=2015-10-11}}</ref>
