{{italic title}} {{about|the pinball game|the franchise|Ripley's Believe It or Not!}} {{Infobox Pinball | title = ''Ripley's Believe It or Not!'' |manufacturer = [[Stern (game company)|Stern]] |image = [[Image:Ripley's Believe It or Not! (pinball).jpg|250px]] |system = |designer= [[Pat Lawlor]], Louis Koziarz |programmer= Louis Koziarz, Greg Dunlap |artwork= John Youssi |mechanics= John Krutsch |music= [[Chris Granner]] |sound= [[Chris Granner]] |release = 2004 |production = }}
'''''Ripley's Believe It or Not!''''' is a [[pinball]] machine produced by [[Stern (game company)|Stern]]. The game is based on the newspaper comic strip of ''[[Ripley's Believe It or Not!]]￼￼''
==Notable features== ''Ripley's Believe It or Not!'' pinball machine is notable for its multi-level rule that enables the beginning player to achieve some of the game's goals early on, while it allows the more advanced player to extend their opportunities with better play. There is also a very strong magnet under the [[shrunken head]] that catches the ball, holds it for a second, then shoots the ball to the rear. In another mode, it stops the ball and immediately gives it back to the lower playfield.<ref name=openkqm>{{cite web| url=http://www.ipdb.org/machine.cgi?id=4917 | work=| title=Internet Pinball Machine Database: Stern 'Ripley's Believe It or Not!®' | first= | last= | date=June 11, 2012}}</ref>
==Digital versions== ''Ripley's Believe It or Not!'' is available as a licensed table of ''[[The Pinball Arcade]]'' for several platforms and was also released for ''[[Stern Pinball Arcade]]''.
